name: Guggs 📷
description: Accredited sports photographer. All things LFC & WWE. XB: 335,645GS / PS: 49 Platinums. #ActuallyAutistic 🧠 🧩
tweet: I don't use it to be left feeling this way, and I certainly didn't expect there to be backlash towards myself for doing what I believed was the right thing, and using the platform I have to speak out against those issues.

name: Guggs 📷
description: Accredited sports photographer. All things LFC & WWE. XB: 335,645GS / PS: 49 Platinums. #ActuallyAutistic 🧠 🧩
tweet: It might not sound like a big deal to anyone else, but I'm unable to process things as a neurotypical person would. I use this space as somewhere to go and share what I'm feeling, or to engage in discussions about my interests.

name: Guggs 📷
description: Accredited sports photographer. All things LFC & WWE. XB: 335,645GS / PS: 49 Platinums. #ActuallyAutistic 🧠 🧩
tweet: The immediate attempt to find my name by a schoolteacher's partner, who must be aware of the importance of respecting privacy, especially (I would hope) of those either vulnerable or with mental disabilities, has left me concerned and extremely anxious.

name: Guggs 📷
description: Accredited sports photographer. All things LFC & WWE. XB: 335,645GS / PS: 49 Platinums. #ActuallyAutistic 🧠 🧩
tweet: This has been extremely disconcerting to me. Fortunately the name I've always given anyone that's asked has always been my middle name. As an autistic person, my privacy surrounding things which others may not feel is an issue, has always been important to me.
